{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> φθον-έω</b>, <br /> <i>aorist</i> ἐφθόνησα, later ἐφθόνεσα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Tob.4.7, “JHS” 46.45 (Athens, 3rd-4th c.AD), “Anthologia Graeca” 5.303, 7.607 (6th c.AD: Palladas Epigrammaticus), 4th-5th c.AD(?): Nonnus Epicus “Dionysiaca” 3.159 \">LXX+3rd c.AD+</a>]:—<i>middle</i>, <i>future</i> in <i>passive</i> sense φθονήσομαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 47.70 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, fut φθονηθήσομαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Hiero” 11.15 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>aorist</i> ἐφθονήθην [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Electra” 30, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 4.2.33, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>perfect</i> <i>participle</i> ἐφθονημένος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Josephus Historicus “Antiquitates Judaicae” 6.11.10, 2nd c.AD: Vettius Valens Astrologus 330.2 \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]: (φθόνος):—<b>bear ill-will</b> or <b>malice, grudge, be envious</b> or <b>jealous,</b> <br /><Level2><b>__I</b></Level2> <i>absolutely</i>, εἴ περ γὰρ φθονέω τε καὶ οὐκ εἰῶ διαπέρσαι, οὐκ ἀνύω φθονέουσα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 4.55, 56 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; κρείττων δόξα τῶν φθονούντων too high for <b>envy,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 3.24 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; εἰ πέφυκε φθονεῖν τὸ θεῖον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"compare (φθονερός 1.2) 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Metaphysica” 982b32: with _accusative_ et\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<i>infinitive</i>, οὔτε τινὰ φθονέω δόμεναι I do not <b>grudge</b> that any should give thee, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 18.16; οὐ φθονῶ σ᾽ ὑπεκφυγεῖν 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 553; τὸ μὲν σὸν οὐ φθονῶ καλῶς ἔχειν 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Medea” 312; ἐφθόνησαν [οἱ θεοὶ] ἄνδρα ἕνα βασιλεῦσαι 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 8.109 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἔφη (i.e. ὁ Σωκράτης) φθονεῖν τοῦς ἐπὶ ταῖς φίλων εὐπραξίαις ἀνιωμένους [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 3.9.8; ὁ φθονῶν ἐπὶ κακοῖς τοῖς τῶν πέλας ἡδόμενος 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Philebus” 48b. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.2</b></Level3> with <i>dative</i> <i>person</i>, πτωχὸς πτωχῷ φθονέει καὶ ἀοιδὸς ἀοιδῷ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Opera et Dies” 26; οὐ φ. ἀγαθοῖς 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 3.71; φ. φασὶ μητρυιὰς τέκνοις 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Ion” 1025; τισὶ φ. καὶ δυσμενῶς ἔχειν 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 12.241, compare 8.13 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; frequently with <i>participle</i> added, φ. τινὶ εὖ πρήσσοντι <b>to envy</b> him for his good fortune, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.236, 237; παιδικοῖς φ. οὐσίαν κεκτημένοις 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 240a, compare 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 27.11 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; without a Noun expressed, καλῶς πράττουσι, πλουτοῦντι φ., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 1.26, 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 21.15, etc.: with _dative_ _of things_, φ. τοῖς ἀγαθοῖς τινος 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 2.4.10 (variant{ἐπὶ τοῖς ἀγ}.,compare 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 1.26; ἐφ᾽ οἷς ἕτεροι ποιήσαντες ἐτιμήθησαν φ. 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 20.151): with _genitive_ _of things_, τοῦ εὐτυχέειν φθονέουσι καὶ τὸ κρέσσον στυγέουσι 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.236 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; οὐδέ τί σε χρὴ ἀλλοτρίων φθονέειν <b>to be envious</b> because of other men's goods [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 18.18 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>dative</i> <i>person</i> et <i>genitive</i> <i>of things</i>, <b>bear a grudge</b> against a person on account of a thing, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hercules Furens” 1309. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.3</b></Level3> <b>resent,</b> with <i>genitive</i>, τῆς δοκήσεως τῶν κερδῶν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.43 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>dative</i> <i>of things</i>, <b>feel righteous indignation at,</b> ταῖς εὐπραγίαις τινῶν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 8.124; also with _dative_ _person_, [prev. author] 4.184, 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 28.18. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__I.3.b</b></Level4> φ. τινὶ followed by ει.., or ἐάν.. <b>take it ill</b> or <b>amiss</b> that.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.146, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 2.4.29 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; μή μοι φθονήσητ᾽, ει.. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Acharnenses” 496: _absolutely_, φ. ἐάν τις.. 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 3.9 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; φθονεῖς ἄπαις οὖσ᾽, εἰ.. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Ion” 1302 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also φ. τινὶ ὅτι.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 3.1.39 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; φ. ὅτι.. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 24.3, uncertain reading in 18.16. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>refuse from feelings of envy</b> or <b>ill-will, grudge,</b> with <i>infinitive</i>, οὐκ ἂν φθονέοιμι ἀγορεῦσαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 11.381; μὴ φθόνει κιρνάμεν 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “I.” 5(4).24; φράσαι 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Medea” 63; σαυτὸν ἐπιδοῦναι 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Thesmophoriazusae” 249 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; μὴ φθονήσῃς is frequently in dialogue, <b>do not refuse</b> to do a thing, μὴ φ. διδάξαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 338a, compare “Hp.Mi.” 372e, “Smp.” 223a; also μὴ φθόνει μοι ἀποκρίνασθαι [prev. author] “Grg.” 489a \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; μὴ φθονήσῃς alone, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Prt.” 320c; δῆλον ὅτι οὐ φθονήσει Ἱππίας ἀποκρίνεσθαι [prev. author] “Hp.Mi.” 363c; οὐδενὶ πώποτε ἐφθόνησα [prev. author] “Ap.” 33a \">Refs</a>]: with <i>participle</i>, μηδέ μοι φθόνει λέγων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 480 (nisi to be read λόγων)\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>accusative</i> et <i>infinitive</i>, τί φθονέεις.. ἀοιδὸν τέρπει; [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 1.346 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>dative</i> et <i>infinitive</i>, τῇ δ᾽ οὐκ ἂν φθονέοιμι.. ἅψασθαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 19.348; οὔτοι φθονῶ σοι δαιμόνων τιμᾶν γένος 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 236. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>grudge, refuse to grant</b> a thing, φθονήσας μήτ᾽ ἀπ᾽ οἰωνῶν φάτιν, μήτ᾽ εἴ τινα.. μαντικῆς ἔχεις ὁδόν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 310: with _dative_ _person_ et _genitive_ _of things_, οὔ τοι ἡμιόνων φθονέω 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 6.68; μηδέ μοι φθονήσῃς εὐγμάτων 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 583 (Lyric poetry), compare 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hecuba” 238; μή μοι φθονήσῃς τοῦ μαθήματος 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Euthydemus” 297b, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 8.4.16; φ. τοῖς ἑαλωκόσι τῆς σωτηρίας 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 6.58.5 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>genitive</i> <i>of things</i> only, <b>to be grudging of</b> a thing, πέπλων, καρποῦ, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hercules Furens” 333, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Menexenus” 238a \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; μηδ᾽ ὀλίγης φθονέσῃς γαίης [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “JHS” [prev. cited] \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <i>passive</i>, <b>to be envied</b> or <b>begrudged,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.52, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 188, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Electra” 30; διὰ σοφίαν φ. ὑπό τινος 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 4.2.33; ἐπ᾽ ἐσθλοῖς 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Fragmenta” 814 (Lyric poetry); φθονηθέντα ὑπὸ Μοίρης “JRS” 18.30 (from Phrygia)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>genitive</i>, <b>to be grudged</b> a thing, φ. τοῦ γάμου ὑπὸ δαιμονίου τινός [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.772b. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G5354","accentedUnicode":"φθονέω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G5355","matchingForm":"φθόνος","stepTransliteration":"fthonos","gloss":"envy","_zh_tw_Gloss":"嫉妒","_es_Gloss":"envidia","_zh_Gloss":"嫉妒"}],"shortDef":"to envy","mediumDef":"<b>to envy, be jealous of</b>; <ref='Gal.5.26'>Gal. 5:26</ref>*","stepGloss":"to envy","stepTransliteration":"fthoneō","count":1,"_es_Definition":"envidiar, estar celoso de","_zh_tw_Definition":"忌妒, 羨慕 (加 5:26)","_zh_Definition":"忌妒, 羡慕 (加 5:26)","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"ganh tị.","_zh_tw_Gloss":"嫉妒","_es_Gloss":"envidiar","_zh_Gloss":"嫉妒"}]}